           Job Description 
           
             Maintenance Mechanic 4  
 PURPOSE:  To provide an array of building equipment operation and maintenance services for the ORAU/ORISE buildings.  Must have journeyman level electrical installation and maintenance skills and a command of the National Electrical Code, NFPA 70. Must possess secondary craft skills in building-related HVAC equipment installation, operation, troubleshooting, and repair.  Must perform plumbing, data, and utility system installation and repair; building access and fire alarm system maintenance and repair; and other maintenance-related activities as assigned by the Maintenance Manager.  Periodically, provide off-hours/emergency call-out services.   
   
 ESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS: 
   
   Troubleshoot and repair electrical equipment and components.  
 
   
   Lead installation and repair of electrical equipment and systems.  
 
   
   Operate and maintain HVAC systems and equipment and automated controls systems.  
 
   
   Perform building equipment preventive maintenance activities.  
 
   
   Install and repair plumbing, data, telecommunications, and other building utility systems.  
 
   
 
   Perform fire alarm and access alarm inspections and maintenance.  
 
 
   REQUIREMENTS:   JOB QUALIFICATIONS:  High School diploma or equivalent with minimum of five years experience in selecting, installing, maintaining, and repairing building electrical equipment and components up to 480V - motors, switchgear, panels, circuit breakers, conduit, wiring, switches,and other electrical components.  Must have a thorough knowledge of NFPA 70, National Electrical Code.  Knowledge of institutional building mechanical and utility systems and their maintenance - plumbing and fixtures, data and telecommunications cabling, etc.  Knowledge of how to safely work on building HVAC and electrical systems and to perform general building maintenance activities in a safe manner.  A current electrician's license required.   Must obtain within three months of hire a City of Oak Ridge electrician's license.  Active Department of Energy (DOE) Q-clearance or the ability to obtain and maintain a DOE Q-clearance.    
 
         
           Career Center 
             
               
 

 
                To develop or access an existing profile and apply for this position, visit the Career Center.  
               
             
           Employment Questions? 
             Call (865) 576-6051, Monday through Friday, from 7:45 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. EDT or e-mail us at  work@orau.gov . 
          
        
       
      
     
    
   
  
 

 
   
 
   
